The paper proposes a novel generative model for relevance search over knowledge graphs, which involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, so cs.DB (Databases) is another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of meta-paths, which are a type of graph-based feature engineering, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the efficiency of the proposed model, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
